The paper discusses the use of advanced AI-related approaches, specifically embedding models, for completing knowledge graphs in the scholarly domain. This suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques. The paper also mentions tasks such as question answering and recommendation, which are commonly associated with information retrieval (cs.IR). The use of embedding models also suggests a focus on deep learning (cs.DL) techniques. Finally, the paper discusses the use of scholarly metadata, which suggests a focus on databases (cs.DB) and information retrieval techniques for scholarly literature.
